Definition.WordDefinition:
Han \Han\ (h[a^]n), contr. inf. & plural pres. of {Haven}. To have; have. [Obs.] --Piers Plowman. [1913 Webster]
Him thanken all, and thus they han an end. --Chaucer. [1913 Webster]
Han n : imperial dynasty that ruled China (most of the time) from 206 BC to 221 and expanded its boundaries and developed its bureaucracy [syn: {Han dynasty}]
